# mimo2codex — local key & runtime config
#
# 1. Copy this file to `.env` (it's gitignored).
# 2. Fill in the keys for the providers you use; leave the rest commented out.
# 3. Load into your shell before running `mimo2codex`:
#      macOS / Linux / Git Bash:   source scripts/load-env.sh
#      Windows PowerShell:         . .\scripts\load-env.ps1
#    Then start the proxy normally:
#      mimo2codex                  # default = MiMo
#      mimo2codex --model ds       # = DeepSeek
#
# Notes:
#   - Lines beginning with `#` and blank lines are ignored.
#   - Values may be quoted with `"` or `'`; surrounding quotes are stripped.
#   - Do NOT commit `.env` — it's already in .gitignore.

# ─────────────── Built-in providers ───────────────

# MiMo (Xiaomi).  Get a key at https://platform.xiaomimimo.com/#/console/api-keys
# sk-* keys auto-route to the pay-as-you-go host; tp-* to token-plan.
# MIMO_API_KEY=sk-xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx

# DeepSeek.  Get a key at https://api-docs.deepseek.com/zh-cn/
# Either name works (DS_API_KEY takes precedence if both are set).
# DS_API_KEY=sk-xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
# DEEPSEEK_API_KEY=sk-xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx

# ─────────────── Generic / third-party OpenAI-compatible upstreams ───────────────
# Single-instance shortcut: declares an ad-hoc generic provider named "generic"
# without editing providers.json. Pair with `mimo2codex --model generic`.
# GENERIC_BASE_URL=https://dashscope.aliyuncs.com/compatible-mode/v1
# GENERIC_API_KEY=sk-xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
# GENERIC_DEFAULT_MODEL=qwen3-max

# Per-provider env keys for providers declared in ~/.mimo2codex/providers.json.
# The key name here must match each provider's `envKey` field.
# QWEN_API_KEY=sk-xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
# KIMI_API_KEY=sk-xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
# GLM_API_KEY=xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
# OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx

# ─────────────── Base URL overrides (optional) ───────────────
# Override the upstream host. Only set these if you need a non-default endpoint
# (e.g. an internal proxy or a regional mirror).
# MIMO_BASE_URL=https://api.xiaomimimo.com/v1
# DEEPSEEK_BASE_URL=https://api.deepseek.com/v1

# ─────────────── mimo2codex runtime settings (optional) ───────────────
# Override the listening host/port. CLI flags (--host / --port) win over env.
# MIMO2CODEX_HOST=127.0.0.1
# MIMO2CODEX_PORT=8788

# Where mimo2codex stores its sqlite DB + admin state. CLI --data-dir wins.
# Default: ~/.mimo2codex/
# MIMO2CODEX_DATA_DIR=~/.mimo2codex

# Override the path to providers.json (the generic-provider declarations).
# Default: <data-dir>/providers.json
# MIMO2CODEX_PROVIDERS_FILE=~/.mimo2codex/providers.json

# Override the default provider id without --model. Built-in choices: mimo / deepseek.
# Generic provider ids also accepted if declared in providers.json.
# MIMO2CODEX_DEFAULT_PROVIDER=mimo

# Hide the `reasoning_content` from the terminal (round-trip to upstream is
# still preserved). Equivalent to passing --no-reasoning. Any non-empty value
# enables this.
# MIMO2CODEX_NO_REASONING=1

# Verbose logging — every request gets logged at INFO. Equivalent to --verbose.
# MIMO2CODEX_VERBOSE=1

# Disable the admin UI + sqlite (read-only stateless mode). Equivalent to --no-admin.
# MIMO2CODEX_NO_ADMIN=1

# How to render upstream "context length exceeded" 400s.
#   friendly (default) — rewrite to a bilingual /compact hint
#   passthrough        — forward the raw upstream error
# MIMO2CODEX_CONTEXT_OVERFLOW_MODE=friendly
